summary: This is an FBI Collected Item Log detailing the execution of a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's New York City residence at 9 East 71st Street on July 11, 2019. The document inventories a large number of digital devices seized, including computers, hard drives, USB drives, phones, tablets, cameras, and CDs/DVDs, as part of the child sex trafficking investigation.

events.title: Search warrant executed at 9 East 71st Street
events.description: A search warrant issued by the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York was executed at Jeffrey Epstein's New York City residence at approximately 2:35 PM. FBI agents seized numerous digital devices.

United States District Court for the Southern District of New York
keyFacts: A search warrant was executed at Jeffrey Epstein's New York City residence (9 East 71st Street) on July 11, 2019, as part of the child sex trafficking investigation.
The search resulted in the seizure of a massive quantity of digital evidence, including multiple computers, hard drives, USB drives, cell phones, tablets, cameras, and CDs/DVDs.
The inventory lists devices found in various rooms (A, B, F, H, FF, GG, II, NN, O, U, V, Y) throughout the residence, indicating a widespread search.
The document is an FBI Collected Item Log (Case ID 31E-NY-3027571) dated July 16, 2019, documenting the evidence seized.
Specific device details like makes, models, and serial numbers were meticulously recorded (e.g., Apple computers, Seagate hard drives, Sony cameras).
